Class SOCDiceResultResources

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.message.SOCMessage
      • soc.message.SOCMessageMulti
        • soc.message.SOCMessageTemplateMi
          • soc.message.SOCDiceResultResources
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, SOCMessageForGame

    public class SOCDiceResultResources
extends SOCMessageTemplateMi
    All known resources gained by players from a dice roll, and their new total resource counts. Server calls buildForGame(SOCGame). Announced to all game members after a SOCDiceResult where players gain resources: For overall sequence, see that message's javadoc.

    Information sent here is gathered from each player's SOCPlayer.getRolledResources(); only players whose rolled resources have nonzero SOCResourceSet.getKnownTotal() are sent. Those players' new resource totals, however, are from SOCPlayer.getResources() .getTotal() which includes any unknown resources.

    Sent from sent as a list of integer parameters with this format: 

     pa[0] = count of players gaining resource(s)
 Per-player sequences consisting of:
   pa[i] = player number gaining resource(s)
   pa[i+1] = new total resource count for that player
   Pair of:
   pa[i+2] = resource amount gained; not 0
   pa[i+3] = resource type gained
   More pairs, if any, for each other resource type gained by the player
   If there are more players after this one:
   pa[i+n] = 0, marking the end of the player's sequence
    The player count parameter helps delimit in case of future expansion of this message's fields.

    Client constructor parses that int parameter list into usable fields like playerNum and playerTotalResources.

    Before v2.0.00 this info was sent as SOCPlayerElement(GAIN) and SOCGameTextMsg, followed by SOCResourceCount. This single message is more efficient and also easier for i18n/localization.

    Since:
    2.0.00
    Author:
    Jeremy D Monin <jeremy@nand.net>

    • Method Detail

      • buildForGame

        public static SOCDiceResultResources buildForGame(SOCGame ga)
        Builder for server to tell clients about players' gained resources and new total counts. Only players with nonzero SOCPlayer.getRolledResources() .getKnownTotal() are included; also skips players having ga.isSeatVacant(pn). Ignores game state.
        Parameters:
        ga - Game to check for rolled resources
        Returns:
        Message for this game's rolled resources, or null if no players gained known resources
